Package: StatBasics
Title: Basic Statistical Concepts Explained Interactively
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-07-06
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Manuel",
           family = "Spinola",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "mspinola10@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7839-1908"))
Description: A didactic, interactive Shiny (golem) application for learning
    fundamental statistical concepts: measures of central tendency and
    dispersion, probability distributions, standard error, confidence
    intervals, correlation, and basic probability. Each module combines
    theory, real datasets, and interactive simulations. It is the
    foundational app of the StatSuite ecosystem, alongside StatModels
    (frequentist), StatML (machine learning), and StatBayes (Bayesian).
